g.text: During the 19th Century the Grau family is very active in business and public life in the city of Kolding, Jutland.The best known family member is Hans Henrik Grau (1816-1885) known as 'Konsul Grau' who was the second oldest son of Johannes Jacobsen Grau and the uncle of Johannes Theodor Grau. (Picture: The Grau general store on Lsbygade, Kolding).

In 1882 Johannes Theodor Grau (1842-1922) is officially granted permission to be merchant in Kolding. Theodor has effectively run the family trading business since 1872 and during that time developed a keen interest in textiles and accessories. He is granted permission to manufacture clothing in Copenhagen in 1894 and sets up his business close to the central train station in the sprawling west end part of town.

Johannes T. Grau is granted permission in 1894 to make clothing and accessories in Copenhagen.He calls his factory on Skydebanegade, Vesterbro: 'Fabrikken Jylland'.In 1894 Johannes T. Grau begins his clothing business in Copenhagen on Reventlowsgade 20, but soon after expands his now fast growing business to Skydebanegade 14.

Reinholdt Sofus Grau (1890-1936) follows his fathers lead from very early on and starts his own business in 1911 making high-quality shirts, lingerie and accessories. Reinholdt dies most unfortunately at an early age in 1936.
The Grau family business on Victoriagade 16 in the western part of Copenhagen as it looked in 1932

g.text: The father of Maria-Louise Grau, Peter J. R. Grau, builds a smaller chain of retail and tailoring stores named 'Adam og Eva'.

Maria-Louise Grau (1969-) is an artisan knitwear designer and an awarded graduate from Danmarks Designskole (1999)with further specialist training at Lineapi Italia and Stoll (2001).Maria-Louise works in Paris for Christian Lacroix ('First line') and trend bureau PeclersParis before establishing her own line of avantgarde knitwear design.The Grau family has been part of the Danish clothing business for five generations.
In 2001 Maria-Louise Grau Starts Grau CPH 1894 with her husband Jan Holm Larsen. Maria-Louise is responsible for the designs and showrooms while Jan is the coordinator of the company.
